Swim for it!

64
00:07:11,083 --> 00:07:13,000
Swim for it!

65
00:07:13,083 --> 00:07:14,708
Why am I doing this?

66
00:07:14,791 --> 00:07:17,083
How can you
breathe in the ocean!

67
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,166
Heads up!

68
00:07:35,791 --> 00:07:37,791
What is the meaning of this?

69
00:07:37,875 --> 00:07:40,875
Can you explain why this
dark stain is here?

70
00:07:40,958 --> 00:07:45,541
It was, the mop bucket.

71
00:07:45,625 --> 00:07:47,166
I spilled it.

72
00:07:47,250 --> 00:07:50,083
Do you know how much
this is going to cost?

73
00:07:54,041 --> 00:07:56,000
Getting away with things
just because you're a child

74
00:07:56,083 --> 00:07:58,375
doesn't fly around
here, young lady.

75
00:08:35,541 --> 00:08:37,916
Towels are for wiping, stupid.

76
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,875
Not for wearing.

77
00:08:39,958 --> 00:08:41,458
Hey, wait!

78
00:08:41,541 --> 00:08:43,458
Stop it!

79
00:08:43,541 --> 00:08:45,083
What are you holding on for?

80
00:08:45,166 --> 00:08:46,833
Just let it go!

81
00:08:46,916 --> 00:08:48,083
No!

82
00:09:03,416 --> 00:09:07,416
This kind of thing
goes on, day in and day out.

83
00:09:42,166 --> 00:09:44,958
Fill up the bag,
and make it snappy.

84
00:09:45,041 --> 00:09:47,250
Otherwise, I open fire
and splatter blood

85
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:50,166
all over this place!

86
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:51,750
March Fifteenth.

87
00:09:51,833 --> 00:09:55,625
Today, someone from the city
is coming to check on me.

88
00:09:57,750 --> 00:09:59,750
But he never really does.

89
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:02,250
He just drops off
the money and leaves.

90
00:10:02,333 --> 00:10:04,000
That's all it ever is.

91
00:10:05,125 --> 00:10:08,333
Hana, I want for you
to have these.

92
00:10:08,416 --> 00:10:10,125
Thank you very much.

93
00:10:15,291 --> 00:10:18,125
Hana, do you remember
the news this morning?

94
00:10:18,208 --> 00:10:20,541
Around here, children in
your situation are forced

95
00:10:20,625 --> 00:10:22,666
to make their living by
either selling their bodies,

96
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:24,666
or selling what's inside them.

97
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:28,416
But you know who it was who
saved you from that fate, right?

98
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:29,875
Yes.

99
00:10:29,958 --> 00:10:31,583
Who was it?

100
00:10:31,666 --> 00:10:34,083
It was, God.

101
00:10:34,166 --> 00:10:36,291
In other words?

102
00:10:36,375 --> 00:10:38,791
It was you, Father.

103
00:10:38,875 --> 00:10:43,416
"Thou shalt not avenge, but
love thy neighbor as thyself."

104
00:10:45,375 --> 00:10:47,416
He just bought me off.

105
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:49,916
Using Maria's hand-me-downs.

106
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:52,166
He totally just bought me off.

107
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:54,916
An update now,
on the bank robbery

108
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,958
that occurred in Paraí-town.

109
00:10:57,041 --> 00:10:59,541
Authorities believe it is
highly likely that the culprit

110
00:10:59,625 --> 00:11:00,791
is Michiko Malandro...

111
00:11:00,875 --> 00:11:03,500
This is a fine piece,
very nice.

112
00:11:03,583 --> 00:11:05,500
It must've set
you back a bit.

113
00:11:05,583 --> 00:11:07,083
Oh my goodness, no.

114
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:09,916
It was a gift from one of the
flock, so the price was right.

115
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,958
Free is always good!

116
00:11:14,375 --> 00:11:16,541
Here you are.

117
00:11:16,625 --> 00:11:18,500
It's nice to see you again.

118
00:11:18,583 --> 00:11:20,916
You look like you're
doing all right, huh?

119
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,250
Yes sir.

120
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:26,416
Good to hear.

121
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:35,416
Ah, thanks.

122
00:11:39,208 --> 00:11:41,833
Are you familiar with
the "Devotee of the Year"?

123
00:11:41,916 --> 00:11:43,875
Sorry, I can't say that I am.

124
00:11:43,958 --> 00:11:45,375
"Dee-vo-tee"?

125
00:11:45,458 --> 00:11:47,291
That's it, right up there.

126
00:11:47,375 --> 00:11:49,250
It's only given to those
who have performed

127
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:51,166
outstanding deeds...

128
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:54,125
And my husband was fortunate
enough to be chosen!

129
00:11:54,208 --> 00:11:55,125
Uh-Huh!

130
00:11:55,208 --> 00:11:56,250
Interesting.

131
00:11:56,333 --> 00:11:58,958
That's quite
a prize you got there.

132
00:11:59,041 --> 00:12:01,125
There was a young man
in the community;

133
00:12:01,208 --> 00:12:04,291
Gonzales was his name,
truly rotten to the core.

134
00:12:04,375 --> 00:12:07,583
But one sermon from Pedro
turned him right around!

135
00:12:07,666 --> 00:12:10,958
Even now, he is an upstanding
member of the flock.

136
00:12:11,041 --> 00:12:13,333
That's impressive!

137
00:12:13,416 --> 00:12:14,750
That's a lie.

138
00:12:21,166 --> 00:12:24,000
The thing about Gonzales,
is he only changed because

139
00:12:24,083 --> 00:12:26,916
of the bullet that was
lodged in his head.

140
00:12:31,041 --> 00:12:34,541
Gonzales, the Lord God loves
you and he forgives you

141
00:12:34,625 --> 00:12:36,916
for all of your transgressions.

142
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:52,166
Ah, what an adorable kitty.

143
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:53,625
Does she belong to you?

144
00:12:53,708 --> 00:12:57,583
Yes, well, Maria took
the poor thing in.

145
00:12:57,666 --> 00:12:58,208
No!

146
00:12:58,291 --> 00:12:59,333
I did!

147
00:12:59,416 --> 00:13:01,166
Sorry dear, is that right?

148
00:13:01,250 --> 00:13:04,208
They just adore
looking after her.

149
00:13:04,291 --> 00:13:05,708
Branco just pooped.

150
00:13:05,791 --> 00:13:07,625
Do something about it.

151
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:11,833
Would you mind taking care
of Branco for me?

152
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:15,166
I've been feeling horribly
lightheaded all day.

153
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:18,041
So, who's on
Branco duty today?

154
00:13:20,666 --> 00:13:22,166
It's my turn.

155
00:13:25,625 --> 00:13:27,833
Never increases, does it?

156
00:13:27,916 --> 00:13:29,375
Christ sakes!

157
00:13:29,458 --> 00:13:32,375
How much do they think it costs
to raise a child these days?

158
00:13:36,041 --> 00:13:37,750
Geez!

159
00:13:39,916 --> 00:13:41,583
Get off!

160
00:13:41,666 --> 00:13:43,791
Ugh, that dirty fleabag!

161
00:13:49,250 --> 00:13:50,333
Chore time!

162
00:13:50,416 --> 00:13:52,541
Go get rid of this for me!

163
00:13:55,166 --> 00:13:56,750
We clear?

164
00:14:12,375 --> 00:14:15,000
Mom, you seen Branco?

165
00:14:15,083 --> 00:14:17,958
No, not all morning,
now that you mention it.

166
00:14:18,041 --> 00:14:20,208
I haven't seen her
since last night.

167
00:14:22,083 --> 00:14:25,166
Hana, have you seen her?

168
00:14:25,250 --> 00:14:26,208
No, sorry.

169
00:14:26,291 --> 00:14:28,208
Well, I find
that hard to believe.

170
00:14:28,291 --> 00:14:32,208
After all, I saw you
take her outside last night.

171
00:14:32,291 --> 00:14:33,916
Where did you take her?

172
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:35,791
Hey!

173
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:40,041
Where did you take Branco?!

174
00:14:45,750 --> 00:14:46,166
C'mon!

175
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:47,416
Giddy-up!

176
00:14:51,208 --> 00:14:52,000
You suck at this!

177
00:14:52,083 --> 00:14:53,541
You have to go faster!

178
00:14:53,625 --> 00:14:56,041
What do we have here?

179
00:14:56,125 --> 00:14:57,833
Look, it's Branco Two.

180
00:14:57,916 --> 00:15:01,208
This Branco looks even filthier
than the first one was.

181
00:15:02,208 --> 00:15:02,958
Ew!

182
00:15:03,041 --> 00:15:04,500
You're gross!

183
00:15:04,583 --> 00:15:05,875
Hang on, Gabe.

184
00:15:05,958 --> 00:15:07,333
I know what we should do.

185
00:15:08,750 --> 00:15:10,916
Branco means
"white," doesn't it?

186
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,875
She's got to be clean.

187
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:19,083
Whoa there, girl!

188
00:15:20,333 --> 00:15:20,791
Aah!

189
00:15:20,875 --> 00:15:22,041
I said "whoa"!

190
00:15:22,125 --> 00:15:23,666
Not so fast!

191
00:15:25,208 --> 00:15:27,541
Hey! Stop moving!

192
00:15:27,625 --> 00:15:28,250
Yeah!

193
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:29,958
Rodeo time, h-yah!

194
00:15:30,041 --> 00:15:32,250
Now, just hold still
for a sec!

195
00:15:39,791 --> 00:15:40,791
That hurt!

196
00:15:40,875 --> 00:15:43,041
Owwww!

197
